ALL Progressives Congress (APC) Professional Women Council has hailed wife of the president, Mrs. Aisha Buhari, and the party’s National Women Leader, Dr. Betta Edu, for supporting women aspirants in 2023. The duo, at a forum, urged the party not to use the excuse of giving women free nomination forms to relegate them to the background. National Director of Women Council Mrs. Ronke Soyombo said Mrs. Buhari’s rejection of relegating women aspirants shows she is a virtuous and a great leader.   ‘My wishes for Nigeria’     ‘Next president should come from South’     Administrator seeks sustainable environment   She urged women to come together, get educated, enlightened and equipped to ensure their full participation in politics aren’t negotiable. The group’s National Director-General, Seyi Bamigbade, thanked her for making the statement that could strengthen the interest of women in politics. He praised the leadership style of APC’s National Chairman Abdullahi Adamu. Bamigbade admonished Nigerians to get their Permanent Voter’s Card (PVCs) as their only weapon to perform their franchise.